{"type":"text","timestamp":1775843275114,"sessionID":"ses_2877fd9baffekiW6mi3Pv8cPCB","part":{"id":"prt_d7880f326001aTN4cdMPH8z3Co","messageID":"msg_d7880dd900012p2oiJvm8sySSH","sessionID":"ses_2877fd9baffekiW6mi3Pv8cPCB","type":"text","text":"Now I'll write the proposal.md for AR-005:","time":{"start":1775843275109,"end":1775843275109}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843275160,"sessionID":"ses_2877fd9baffekiW6mi3Pv8cPCB","part":{"id":"prt_d7881f16c001O239uKLlTW6WIJ","messageID":"msg_d7880dd900012p2oiJvm8sySSH","sessionID":"ses_2877fd9baffekiW6mi3Pv8cPCB","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-44a2533cba664754a86aa80d241c96d1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-005/proposal.md","content":"# AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement HTTP handlers for sandbox creation endpoints (`POST /v1/agent-runtime` and `POST /v1/code-interpreter`) in the workload manager. These handlers convert user-provided AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter CRD references into actual Kubernetes Sandbox/SandboxClaim resources, orchestrate the creation lifecycle (wait for running status, resolve Pod IP, persist session metadata), and return session identifiers for downstream routing.\n\nCore responsibilities:\n1. **Request Validation**: Parse and validate `CreateSandboxRequest` JSON (kind override, name/namespace required)\n2. **Template Resolution**: Fetch AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter from client-go informer cache\n3. **Sandbox Assembly**: Build Sandbox/SandboxClaim objects from workload templates\n4. **Creation Orchestration**: Register watcher, create CR, wait for running status (max 2 minutes)\n5. **Post-Creation**: Resolve Pod IP, build entry points, persist to Store, respond to client\n6. **Error Handling**: Rollback on timeout or failure (delete CR, remove Store placeholder)\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` | HTTP handlers: `handleAgentRuntimeCreate`, `handleCodeInterpreterCreate`, `handleDeleteSandbox` |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` | Sandbox/SandboxClaim object construction from CRD templates |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator.go` | Creation orchestration: watcher registration, CR creation, timeout handling, rollback |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/informers.go` | client-go SharedInformerFactory integration for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter listers |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_controller.go` | SandboxReconciler with `WatchSandboxOnce` for status notifications |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client.go` | K8sClient wrapper: dynamic client, client-go typed client, pod informer |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | Constants: DefaultSandboxTTL, DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout, label/annotation keys |\n| Test files | `*_test.go` for each source file (handlers, builder, creator, controller, client) |\n\n### API Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Handler | Description |\n|--------|------|---------|-------------|\n| POST | `/v1/agent-runtime` | `handleAgentRuntimeCreate` | Create sandbox from AgentRuntime template |\n| POST | `/v1/code-interpreter` | `handleCodeInterpreterCreate` | Create sandbox from CodeInterpreter template |\n| DELETE | `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId` | `handleDeleteSandbox` | Delete sandbox by session ID |\n| DELETE | `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId` | `handleDeleteSandbox` | Delete sandbox by session ID |\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Router deployment (`cmd/router`) and session routing logic\n- Agentd idle cleanup controller (`cmd/agentd`)\n- CRD type definitions (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`) — AR-001\n- client-go code generation — handled by `make gen-client`\n- Helm chart and deployment manifests\n- E2E integration test fixtures (handled in separate test task)\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Upstream Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Impact |\n|------------|--------|\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Typed clients for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter; informers provide local cache; listers for read queries |\n| `k8s.io/client-go/dynamic` | Create/delete Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRs (external CRDs from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox`) |\n| `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` | Pod lister for IP resolution |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | SandboxReconciler watches Sandbox status changes |\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | Store interface for session persistence |\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | HTTP framework for API endpoints |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | CRD type definitions (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, TargetPort) |\n| `pkg/common/types` | Shared types (CreateSandboxRequest, CreateSandboxResponse, SandboxInfo) |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| Router (`cmd/router`) | Uses `sessionId` from response to route HTTP traffic to sandbox Pod IP |\n| Agentd (`cmd/agentd`) | Reads Store records for idle/expired sandbox cleanup |\n| GC loop (`pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`) | Queries Store for inactive/expired sessions |\n| Auth middleware | Injects context keys (`userToken`, `namespace`, `serviceAccountName`) for per-user client |\n| E2E tests | Validates creation success, timeout rollback, error responses |\n| Helm chart | Configures `EnableAuth`, `EnableTLS`, `Port` flags affecting handler behavior |\n\n### Breaking Change Considerations\n\n- **API Contract Stability**: Response schema (`CreateSandboxResponse`) must remain stable; adding fields is safe, removing fields breaks clients\n- **Timeout Constants**: `2-minute creation timeout` and `30-second delete timeout` are spec-required; changing these affects client retry behavior\n- **Session ID Format**: UUID format is documented; clients may parse/store it\n- **WarmPool Path**: `WarmPoolSize > 0` triggers SandboxClaim creation; changing this logic affects warm pool consumers\n- **Auth Integration**: Per-user dynamic client behavior when `EnableAuth=true` must match spec\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Use Typed Sandbox Client Instead of Dynamic Client\n\n**Approach**: Generate typed client for Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRDs within agentcube's client-go.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Type safety; IDE support; informer generation for Sandbox |\n| Cons | Sandbox/SandboxClaim belong to `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` (external dependency); adding to agentcube client-go creates maintenance burden; version mismatch risk |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Dynamic client with `unstructured.Unstructured` is the standard pattern for external CRDs.\n\n### Alternative 2: Skip Store Placeholder Before CR Creation\n\n**Approach**: Create CR first, then store placeholder only after CR creation succeeds.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Simpler flow; no rollback needed for Store if CR creation fails |\n| Cons | No idempotency check during creation window; GC cannot track in-progress creation; watcher registration before CR creates race condition risk |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Store placeholder before CR creation enables idempotency, GC awareness, and rollback target.\n\n### Alternative 3: Poll Sandbox Status Instead of Watcher\n\n**Approach**: After CR creation, poll `GET` Sandbox status every 5 seconds until `running`.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | No reconciler dependency; simpler implementation |\n| Cons | Higher API load; potential missed events; less responsive (5s latency vs instant notification); wastes API quota |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. `WatchSandboxOnce` via reconciler provides immediate notification and lower API load.\n\n### Alternative 4: Separate Handlers for AgentRuntime vs CodeInterpreter\n\n**Approach**: Use distinct handler structs (`AgentRuntimeHandler`, `CodeInterpreterHandler`) instead of shared `handleDeleteSandbox`.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Clearer separation; independent unit testing |\n| Cons | Duplicated delete logic; both endpoints use same session lookup; spec requires shared handler |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. DELETE endpoints share identical session lookup and CR deletion logic per spec.\n\n### Alternative 5: Embedded Template in Request Instead of CRD Reference\n\n**Approach**: Accept full PodSpec in request body instead of referencing existing AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | No CRD lookup; simpler request validation |\n| Cons | No workload template management; no reusable definitions; larger request bodies; loses K8s-native resource model |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. CRD references enable workload template management, RBAC per workload, and K8s-native integration.\n\n## Risks\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Informer cache stale (AgentRuntime not found after creation) | Use `informer.WaitForCacheSync` at startup; fallback to direct API GET on cache miss (log warning) |\n| Watcher channel full (missed running notification) | Use buffered channel (size 1); non-blocking send with `default` branch logs warning |\n| Pod IP resolution fails (sandbox running but no PodIP) | Return error with rollback; Pod IP appears within seconds after Running phase—retry loop 3× with 5s interval |\n| Store unavailable during placeholder write | Ping store at startup; if Store fails during creation, return 503 (ServiceUnavailable) |\n| Timeout after CR creation but before rollback completes | Use independent 30s context for delete; log error if delete fails, rely on GC cleanup |\n| Concurrent creation for same workload (race condition) | Use Store placeholder as idempotency lock; check Store before creation |\n| Auth middleware context keys missing (EnableAuth=true) | Validate context keys exist before using per-user client; fallback to default client with warning |\n| WarmPool SandboxClaim vs Sandbox kind mismatch | Track `Kind` in `SandboxInfo`; delete handler switches GVR based on stored Kind |\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n1. **client-go Integration Pattern**:\n   - `informers/externalversions.SharedInformerFactory` → `Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Lister()`\n   - `informers/externalversions.SharedInformerFactory` → `Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters().Lister()`\n   - `clientset/versioned/fake.NewSimpleClientset()` for unit tests\n\n2. **GVR Constants**:\n   ```go\n   AgentRuntimeGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"agentruntimes\"}\n   CodeInterpreterGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"codeinterpreters\"}\n   SandboxGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxes\"}\n   SandboxClaimGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxclaims\"}\n   ```\n\n3. **Watcher Registration Order**: Must call `WatchSandboxOnce` BEFORE `dynamicClient.Create` to avoid race condition.\n\n4. **Timeout Configuration**:\n   - Sandbox creation wait: 2 minutes (spec-required)\n   - Rollback CR delete: 30 seconds\n   - GC single tick: 2 minutes\n\n5. **Pod IP Resolution Strategy**:\n   - Primary: Pod name = sandbox name, read from `podLister`\n   - Annotation fallback: `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name` annotation on Sandbox\n   - Label fallback: List pods by `runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name=<sandboxName>`, match owner reference\n\n6. **JSON Response Format**: Use `{\"message\": \"...\"}` for all error responses per spec.\n\n7. **CodeInterpreter Defaults**:\n   - Empty `Ports`: Default to `[{Port: 8080, Protocol: HTTP, PathPrefix: \"/\"}]`\n   - Empty `AuthMode`: Default to `\"picod\"`\n   - `WarmPoolSize > 0`: Create SandboxClaim instead of Sandbox\n\n## References\n\n- Spec: `sandbox-orchestration/spec.md`\n- Design: `sandbox-orchestration/AR-005-sandbox-creation-processor/design.md`\n- client-go Reference: `deployment/client-go.md`\n- CRD Types: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`, `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n- Shared Types: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go`\n- Project Context: `project.md`\n- Kubernetes API Conventions: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md\n- agent-sandbox API: https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox\n- Kubebuilder Book: https://book.kubebuilder.io/"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/config_test.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":37,"character":14},"end":{"line":37,"character":14}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field WriteTimeout"},{"range":{"start":{"line":38,"character":13},"end":{"line":38,"character":13}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field IdleTimeout"},{"range":{"start":{"line":39,"character":17},"end":{"line":39,"character":17}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field ShutdownTimeout"},{"range":{"start":{"line":40,"character":15},"end":{"line":40,"character":15}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field EnableHealthz"},{"range":{"start":{"line":41,"character":14},"end":{"line":41,"character":14}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field EnableReadyz"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/go.mod":[{"range":{"start":{"line":12,"character":34},"end":{"line":12,"character":45}},"severity":2,"source":"go mod tidy","message":"github.com/go-chi/chi/v5 should be direct"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/router.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/handler.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/server.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/config.go":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-005/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-005/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775843275138,"end":1775843275157}}}}
