{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843279386,"sessionID":"ses_2877fd9baffekiW6mi3Pv8cPCB","part":{"id":"prt_d788201cb001ZCZki1F6UqcIHr","messageID":"msg_d7881f1e1001LHf6EN3TaeJkoS","sessionID":"ses_2877fd9baffekiW6mi3Pv8cPCB","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-776fd1a11ee24b349e8d948444eabd8b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-005/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-005/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 Proposal\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Implement HTTP handlers for sandbox creation endpoints (`POST /v1/agent-runtime` and `POST /v1/code-interpreter`) in the workload manager. These handlers convert user-provided AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter CRD references into actual Kubernetes Sandbox/SandboxClaim resources, orchestrate the creation lifecycle (wait for running status, resolve Pod IP, persist session metadata), and return session identifiers for downstream routing.\n6: \n7: Core responsibilities:\n8: 1. **Request Validation**: Parse and validate `CreateSandboxRequest` JSON (kind override, name/namespace required)\n9: 2. **Template Resolution**: Fetch AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter from client-go informer cache\n10: 3. **Sandbox Assembly**: Build Sandbox/SandboxClaim objects from workload templates\n11: 4. **Creation Orchestration**: Register watcher, create CR, wait for running status (max 2 minutes)\n12: 5. **Post-Creation**: Resolve Pod IP, build entry points, persist to Store, respond to client\n13: 6. **Error Handling**: Rollback on timeout or failure (delete CR, remove Store placeholder)\n14: \n15: ## Scope\n16: \n17: ### In Scope\n18: \n19: | Deliverable | Description |\n20: |-------------|-------------|\n21: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` | HTTP handlers: `handleAgentRuntimeCreate`, `handleCodeInterpreterCreate`, `handleDeleteSandbox` |\n22: | `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` | Sandbox/SandboxClaim object construction from CRD templates |\n23: | `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator.go` | Creation orchestration: watcher registration, CR creation, timeout handling, rollback |\n24: | `pkg/workloadmanager/informers.go` | client-go SharedInformerFactory integration for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter listers |\n25: | `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_controller.go` | SandboxReconciler with `WatchSandboxOnce` for status notifications |\n26: | `pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client.go` | K8sClient wrapper: dynamic client, client-go typed client, pod informer |\n27: | `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | Constants: DefaultSandboxTTL, DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout, label/annotation keys |\n28: | Test files | `*_test.go` for each source file (handlers, builder, creator, controller, client) |\n29: \n30: ### API Endpoints\n31: \n32: | Method | Path | Handler | Description |\n33: |--------|------|---------|-------------|\n34: | POST | `/v1/agent-runtime` | `handleAgentRuntimeCreate` | Create sandbox from AgentRuntime template |\n35: | POST | `/v1/code-interpreter` | `handleCodeInterpreterCreate` | Create sandbox from CodeInterpreter template |\n36: | DELETE | `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId` | `handleDeleteSandbox` | Delete sandbox by session ID |\n37: | DELETE | `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId` | `handleDeleteSandbox` | Delete sandbox by session ID |\n38: \n39: ### Out of Scope\n40: \n41: - Router deployment (`cmd/router`) and session routing logic\n42: - Agentd idle cleanup controller (`cmd/agentd`)\n43: - CRD type definitions (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`) — AR-001\n44: - client-go code generation — handled by `make gen-client`\n45: - Helm chart and deployment manifests\n46: - E2E integration test fixtures (handled in separate test task)\n47: \n48: ## Impact Analysis\n49: \n50: ### Upstream Dependencies\n51: \n52: | Dependency | Impact |\n53: |------------|--------|\n54: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Typed clients for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter; informers provide local cache; listers for read queries |\n55: | `k8s.io/client-go/dynamic` | Create/delete Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRs (external CRDs from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox`) |\n56: | `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` | Pod lister for IP resolution |\n57: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | SandboxReconciler watches Sandbox status changes |\n58: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | Store interface for session persistence |\n59: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | HTTP framework for API endpoints |\n60: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | CRD type definitions (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, TargetPort) |\n61: | `pkg/common/types` | Shared types (CreateSandboxRequest, CreateSandboxResponse, SandboxInfo) |\n62: \n63: ### Downstream Consumers\n64: \n65: | Consumer | Usage |\n66: |----------|-------|\n67: | Router (`cmd/router`) | Uses `sessionId` from response to route HTTP traffic to sandbox Pod IP |\n68: | Agentd (`cmd/agentd`) | Reads Store records for idle/expired sandbox cleanup |\n69: | GC loop (`pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`) | Queries Store for inactive/expired sessions |\n70: | Auth middleware | Injects context keys (`userToken`, `namespace`, `serviceAccountName`) for per-user client |\n71: | E2E tests | Validates creation success, timeout rollback, error responses |\n72: | Helm chart | Configures `EnableAuth`, `EnableTLS`, `Port` flags affecting handler behavior |\n73: \n74: ### Breaking Change Considerations\n75: \n76: - **API Contract Stability**: Response schema (`CreateSandboxResponse`) must remain stable; adding fields is safe, removing fields breaks clients\n77: - **Timeout Constants**: `2-minute creation timeout` and `30-second delete timeout` are spec-required; changing these affects client retry behavior\n78: - **Session ID Format**: UUID format is documented; clients may parse/store it\n79: - **WarmPool Path**: `WarmPoolSize > 0` triggers SandboxClaim creation; changing this logic affects warm pool consumers\n80: - **Auth Integration**: Per-user dynamic client behavior when `EnableAuth=true` must match spec\n81: \n82: ## Alternatives Considered\n83: \n84: ### Alternative 1: Use Typed Sandbox Client Instead of Dynamic Client\n85: \n86: **Approach**: Generate typed client for Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRDs within agentcube's client-go.\n87: \n88: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n89: |--------|------------|\n90: | Pros | Type safety; IDE support; informer generation for Sandbox |\n91: | Cons | Sandbox/SandboxClaim belong to `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` (external dependency); adding to agentcube client-go creates maintenance burden; version mismatch risk |\n92: \n93: **Decision**: Rejected. Dynamic client with `unstructured.Unstructured` is the standard pattern for external CRDs.\n94: \n95: ### Alternative 2: Skip Store Placeholder Before CR Creation\n96: \n97: **Approach**: Create CR first, then store placeholder only after CR creation succeeds.\n98: \n99: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n100: |--------|------------|\n101: | Pros | Simpler flow; no rollback needed for Store if CR creation fails |\n102: | Cons | No idempotency check during creation window; GC cannot track in-progress creation; watcher registration before CR creates race condition risk |\n103: \n104: **Decision**: Rejected. Store placeholder before CR creation enables idempotency, GC awareness, and rollback target.\n105: \n106: ### Alternative 3: Poll Sandbox Status Instead of Watcher\n107: \n108: **Approach**: After CR creation, poll `GET` Sandbox status every 5 seconds until `running`.\n109: \n110: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n111: |--------|------------|\n112: | Pros | No reconciler dependency; simpler implementation |\n113: | Cons | Higher API load; potential missed events; less responsive (5s latency vs instant notification); wastes API quota |\n114: \n115: **Decision**: Rejected. `WatchSandboxOnce` via reconciler provides immediate notification and lower API load.\n116: \n117: ### Alternative 4: Separate Handlers for AgentRuntime vs CodeInterpreter\n118: \n119: **Approach**: Use distinct handler structs (`AgentRuntimeHandler`, `CodeInterpreterHandler`) instead of shared `handleDeleteSandbox`.\n120: \n121: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n122: |--------|------------|\n123: | Pros | Clearer separation; independent unit testing |\n124: | Cons | Duplicated delete logic; both endpoints use same session lookup; spec requires shared handler |\n125: \n126: **Decision**: Rejected. DELETE endpoints share identical session lookup and CR deletion logic per spec.\n127: \n128: ### Alternative 5: Embedded Template in Request Instead of CRD Reference\n129: \n130: **Approach**: Accept full PodSpec in request body instead of referencing existing AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter.\n131: \n132: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n133: |--------|------------|\n134: | Pros | No CRD lookup; simpler request validation |\n135: | Cons | No workload template management; no reusable definitions; larger request bodies; loses K8s-native resource model |\n136: \n137: **Decision**: Rejected. CRD references enable workload template management, RBAC per workload, and K8s-native integration.\n138: \n139: ## Risks\n140: \n141: | Risk | Mitigation |\n142: |------|------------|\n143: | Informer cache stale (AgentRuntime not found after creation) | Use `informer.WaitForCacheSync` at startup; fallback to direct API GET on cache miss (log warning) |\n144: | Watcher channel full (missed running notification) | Use buffered channel (size 1); non-blocking send with `default` branch logs warning |\n145: | Pod IP resolution fails (sandbox running but no PodIP) | Return error with rollback; Pod IP appears within seconds after Running phase—retry loop 3× with 5s interval |\n146: | Store unavailable during placeholder write | Ping store at startup; if Store fails during creation, return 503 (ServiceUnavailable) |\n147: | Timeout after CR creation but before rollback completes | Use independent 30s context for delete; log error if delete fails, rely on GC cleanup |\n148: | Concurrent creation for same workload (race condition) | Use Store placeholder as idempotency lock; check Store before creation |\n149: | Auth middleware context keys missing (EnableAuth=true) | Validate context keys exist before using per-user client; fallback to default client with warning |\n150: | WarmPool SandboxClaim vs Sandbox kind mismatch | Track `Kind` in `SandboxInfo`; delete handler switches GVR based on stored Kind |\n151: \n152: ## Implementation Notes\n153: \n154: 1. **client-go Integration Pattern**:\n155:    - `informers/externalversions.SharedInformerFactory` → `Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Lister()`\n156:    - `informers/externalversions.SharedInformerFactory` → `Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters().Lister()`\n157:    - `clientset/versioned/fake.NewSimpleClientset()` for unit tests\n158: \n159: 2. **GVR Constants**:\n160:    ```go\n161:    AgentRuntimeGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"agentruntimes\"}\n162:    CodeInterpreterGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"codeinterpreters\"}\n163:    SandboxGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxes\"}\n164:    SandboxClaimGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxclaims\"}\n165:    ```\n166: \n167: 3. **Watcher Registration Order**: Must call `WatchSandboxOnce` BEFORE `dynamicClient.Create` to avoid race condition.\n168: \n169: 4. **Timeout Configuration**:\n170:    - Sandbox creation wait: 2 minutes (spec-required)\n171:    - Rollback CR delete: 30 seconds\n172:    - GC single tick: 2 minutes\n173: \n174: 5. **Pod IP Resolution Strategy**:\n175:    - Primary: Pod name = sandbox name, read from `podLister`\n176:    - Annotation fallback: `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name` annotation on Sandbox\n177:    - Label fallback: List pods by `runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name=<sandboxName>`, match owner reference\n178: \n179: 6. **JSON Response Format**: Use `{\"message\": \"...\"}` for all error responses per spec.\n180: \n181: 7. **CodeInterpreter Defaults**:\n182:    - Empty `Ports`: Default to `[{Port: 8080, Protocol: HTTP, PathPrefix: \"/\"}]`\n183:    - Empty `AuthMode`: Default to `\"picod\"`\n184:    - `WarmPoolSize > 0`: Create SandboxClaim instead of Sandbox\n185: \n186: ## References\n187: \n188: - Spec: `sandbox-orchestration/spec.md`\n189: - Design: `sandbox-orchestration/AR-005-sandbox-creation-processor/design.md`\n190: - client-go Reference: `deployment/client-go.md`\n191: - CRD Types: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`, `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n192: - Shared Types: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go`\n193: - Project Context: `project.md`\n194: - Kubernetes API Conventions: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md\n195: - agent-sandbox API: https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox\n196: - Kubebuilder Book: https://book.kubebuilder.io/\n\n(End of file - total 196 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement HTTP handlers for sandbox creation endpoints (`POST /v1/agent-runtime` and `POST /v1/code-interpreter`) in the workload manager. These handlers convert user-provided AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter CRD references into actual Kubernetes Sandbox/SandboxClaim resources, orchestrate the creation lifecycle (wait for running status, resolve Pod IP, persist session metadata), and return session identifiers for downstream routing.\n\nCore responsibilities:\n1. **Request Validation**: Parse and validate `CreateSandboxRequest` JSON (kind override, name/namespace required)\n2. **Template Resolution**: Fetch AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter from client-go informer cache\n3. **Sandbox Assembly**: Build Sandbox/SandboxClaim objects from workload templates\n4. **Creation Orchestration**: Register watcher, create CR, wait for running status (max 2 minutes)\n5. **Post-Creation**: Resolve Pod IP, build entry points, persist to Store, respond to client\n6. **Error Handling**: Rollback on timeout or failure (delete CR, remove Store placeholder)\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-005/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775843279376,"end":1775843279383}}}}
